By the polypus is here meant a swelling in the hollow of the nostrils, which either grows downwards and dilates the nostrils so as to deform the visage, or else, taking an opposite direction, extends into the fauces and produces danger of strangulation. In both cases a very ,offen- sive smell is emitted.
